<TITLE> Best Air launches Dubai flight Aug 27 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 13 (bdnews24.com)  Private airline Best Air is set to launch flights from Dhaka to Dubai on Aug 27, an airline official said Wednesday. Farhad Hossain, director (Sales and Marketing) of the airline, told bdnews24.com that Best Air would operate four round flights to the city in the UAE a weekSunday, Monday, Wednesday and Thursday. The airlines hired a MD 83 for the route. "Many Bangladeshi labourers work in the city. The Best Air has taken the decision to start flight operation on the route keeping that in mind," Farhad said. According to data available on the website of expatriates' welfare and overseas employment ministry, over 8.1 lakh Bangladeshis have been working in the UAE. Among the local airliners, only Biman Bangladesh Airlines operates flight on the Dhaka-Dubai route. GMG airlines had started operation but stopped in July. On January 14, Best Air started its journey with a leased Boeing 737 through running a flight on Dhaka-Chittagong route. It made its debut on international route on May 25 through the flight from Dhaka to Bangkok. Best Air started operating on Dhaka-Colombo-Male' route on July 28. Farhad said the airline's flights to Kuala Lumpur would take off soon. Two more aircraftsAirbus A-321 and ERG-145 would be added to Best Air's fleet by September, another Best Air official said. The private airline has permission to fly to 11 international destinations including Dhaka-Kunming, Dhaka- Kathmandu, Dhaka-Bahrain. bdnews24.c
